critique: This document is an executive order that amends a previous executive order regarding the jurisdiction of the Canal Zone judiciary. It primarily deals with defining the geographical boundaries of the Balboa and Cristobal Divisions of the District Court of the Canal Zone. There is no direct indication of ideological tilt, immigration approach, national security concerns, economic regulation, or social inclusion. The order does not seem to expand executive power significantly, as it mainly clarifies existing jurisdictional boundaries. It also doesn't appear to shift power between state and federal entities, as it pertains to a specific territory under federal control. Therefore, most axes should be scored as neutral.
